# .trivyignore — Trivy vulnerability allow-list
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line (e.g. CVE-2024-12345).
# Blank lines and lines starting with '#' are ignored.
#
# Allow-list policy:
#   Before adding an entry, document:
#     - CVE ID
#     - Rationale: why this finding is acceptable (e.g. not reachable in
#       molecule test context, OS vendor won't fix, mitigated elsewhere)
#     - Expiry: date after which this entry must be re-evaluated (ISO 8601)
#     - Owner: who approved the exception
#
# Example entry (do not uncomment without review):
#   # CVE-2024-99999
#   # Rationale: affects libfoo only when compiled with --enable-bar,
#   #            which the distro package does not do.
#   # Expiry: 2026-11-01
#   # Owner: pochaev.nik@gmail.com
#   CVE-2024-99999
#
# Reference: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore
#
# No entries yet. Add only after operator review and with the fields above.
